				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6367687#post-4250357</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6367687/scp-3496#post-4250357</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 15 May 2019 22:08:19 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Monteparnas</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2926286</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Good skip, all in all, upvoted already.</p> <p>What makes WWS specially interesting, and it is very clear in this piece, is how they are <strong>not</strong> wacky and delusional in their intent to do good. They are devoted to do good and are quite informal, but they are not delusional about that.</p> <p>Mana would, in their place, just start releasing whatever the mask produces in the wild if seem as good and only stop if some proof of it going bad is shown to them. Wilson's call first dibs on the opportunity, but they will still make a careful study of the effects on controlled environment first, because they know they are messing with something not understood.</p> <p>I don't know if this approach would work for big groups like Mana, but it is a nice change of pace.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
